She says she was 'horrified' in the days before Robbie was burned because Collins had been 'stalking' her son as she testified on the witness stand, reports FOX26.

Almost 17 years later, and despite the fact that he died in 2011, the jury will hear a videotaped deposition from Robert in which he accuses Collins of raping him two weeks before setting him on fire.

'He took me out into the woods where I was burned. It was the same place. He took my clothes down and started raping me,' Robert reportedly says in the 30-minute recording.

Collins, now 29, was convicted of sexually assaulting a different 8-year-old boy in 2001.

A judge determined last March that he could be tried for murder as an adult, despite being a teenager at the time.

